  "market_context": "RBOB Gasoline futures opening a new weekly candle on Monday with the draw on liquidity identified as the range highs above. A failure swing divergence existed but was not considered relevant until price showed intent to expand away from it.",
  "key_observation": "First three days of the week expanded creating a daily fair value gap; Thursday retraced back into the weekly range printing a reversal, while the correlated crude oil market produced an SMT divergence with a gap, validating the key level.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Mark out the weekly profile starting from Monday's open and identify the draw on liquidity as the range highs above.",
    "Step 2: Note the failure swing divergence but disregard it until price prints a reversal signature confirming expansion away.",
    "Step 3: Observe that Monday-Wednesday expanded creating a daily fair value gap on RB.",
    "Step 4: Identify Thursday retracing back into the weekly range and printing a reversal candle.",
    "Step 5: Cross-reference the correlated crude oil market and confirm SMT divergence with a gap (SMT with a key level).",
    "Step 6: Use that key level to project price toward the overall draw on liquidity (the range high).",
    "Step 7: After candle closure, mark out the equilibrium (EQ) of the previous day's range and anticipate the next day's low forming within the upper half.",
    "Step 8: Drop down for a daily profile to confirm the bullish narrative for execution."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
